TY  - JOUR
AU  - Thornton, Daniel L.
AU  - Valente, Giorgio
T1  - Out-of-Sample Predictions of Bond Excess Returns and Forward Rates: An Asset Allocation Perspective
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs069
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 10
SP  - 3141
EP  - 3168
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article investigates the out-of-sample predictability of bond excess returns. We assess the economic value of the forecasting ability of empirical models based on long-term forward interest rates in a dynamic asset allocation strategy. The results show that the information content of forward rates does not generate systematic economic value to investors. Indeed, these models do not outperform the no-predictability benchmark. Furthermore, their relative performance deteriorates over time.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs069
ER  - 



