AU  - Keloharju, Matti
AU  - Knüpfer, Samuli
AU  - Linnainmaa, Juhani
T1  - Do Investors Buy What They Know? Product Market Choices and Investment Decisions
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs090
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 10
SP  - 2921
EP  - 2958
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article shows that individuals' product market choices influence their investment decisions. Using microdata from the brokerage and automotive industries, we find a strong positive relation between customer relationship, ownership of a company, and size of the ownership stake. Investors are also more likely to purchase and less likely to sell shares of companies they frequent as customers. These effects are stronger for individuals with longer customer relationships. A merger-based natural experiment supports a causal interpretation of our results. We also find evidence of causality in the other direction: inheritances and gifts have an effect on individuals' patronage decisions. A setup in which customer-investors regard stocks as consumption goods, not just as investments, seems to best explain our results. (JEL G11, G24, D83)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs090
ER  - 



